snippet.textDisplay: This wouldn't be near as big of an issue if B550 had been out when Zen2 launched. They've let everyone continue to buy B450 boards with the promise of future upgrades that they now say won't happen. AMD previously stated that we'd have 4 generations of Ryzen on AM4 with forwards compatibility. Zen/Zen+/Zen2 doesn't equal 4.That's why people are mad and the decision honestly doesn't even make sense. We're getting AM5 in 2021 so why not wait until AM5 and fulfill your promise? There's literally no reason to upgrade to Zen3 when it requires a new board because it's effectively a dead end. AM5 is right around the corner.
